title: Palettes and Themes
type: text/vnd.tiddlywiki

Palettes and themes both affect the appearance of a wiki, and are designed to be independent of one another.

* A [[colour palette|ColourPalettes]] supplies the colour values used to display the wiki
* A theme is a plugin containing stylesheets that control layout, typography and spacing

Any theme can be combined with any palette. Both can be chosen in the <<.controlpanel-tab Appearance>> tab of the control panel.

This separation only works if themes and palettes respect it:

* Themes should obtain their colours from the current palette with the <<.mlink colour>> function, rather than hard coding colour values in their stylesheets
* If a theme needs a colour that the common palettes do not define, it should provide a fallback via a [[$:/config/DefaultColourMappings/|colour Macro]] tiddler rather than assuming a particular palette is selected
* Palettes should confine themselves to colour values, and avoid entries that encode layout or theme-specific presentation

A wiki following these practices lets its users freely mix palettes and themes, including palettes with [[automatic dark and light schemes|Automatic Palette Switching]].
